        <svcsubproc id="x08290085">
            <title>Fault Detection/ Management</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The testing method for troubleshooting the electrical systems portrayed in this manual is a
                        basic voltage test. An alternative method of checking for voltage drops within a given circuit
                        may be a quicker method of identifying an exact problem.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>A short in the ammeter gauge circuits will be apparent when the ammeter gauge points straight down.
            </para>
            <para>Problems in the ammeter circuits could be the result of an open or shorted gauge, open circuits,
                shorted circuits, a failure in the ESC, a problem in the PAM or a problem with wiring to and from the
                PAM.
            </para>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08290_X08290193.xml" xrefid="x08290193">Pyrometer/ Ammeter Module (PAM)</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="x08290193"/>.
            </para>
